First Read: 10-Mar-26
HJR217 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 COMMENDING HOUSTON COUNTY SHERIFF'S LIEUTENANT ROBERT
4 HOPKINS FOR RECEIVING THE LEGISLATIVE MEDAL OF HONOR FOR LAW
5 ENFORCEMENT OFFICERS.
6
7 WHEREAS, with highest respect and most sincere
8 admiration, we commend Houston County Sheriff's Lieutenant
9 Robert Hopkins for earning the Legislative Medal of Honor
10 for Law Enforcement Officers; and
11 WHEREAS, Lieutenant Hopkins was nominated for this
12 honor by Houston County Sheriff Donald J. Valenza; he has
13 consistently demonstrated extraordinary courage,
14 professionalism, and dedication to public service, but on
15 October 12, 2025, he displayed exceptional bravery and
16 selflessness during a critical incident that occurred while
17 he was working an off-duty detail in Dothan, Alabama; and
18 WHEREAS, on that afternoon, Lieutenant Hopkins heard
19 gunshots emanating from the mall entrance of Dillard's; as
20 he exited the store, he observed a male who had been shot
21 and was lying in front of the barbershop entrance; several
22 bystanders informed Lieutenant Hopkins that the gunman had
23 fled into the barbershop; after relaying this information
24 and his location to dispatch, Lieutenant Hopkins pulled the
25 injured man away from the entrance; a United States Army
26 veteran offered assistance, so Lieutenant Hopkins instructed
27 him to retrieve the first aid bag from his patrol car; and
28 WHEREAS, shortly after, a Dothan police officer
Page 1

WHEREAS, shortly after, a Dothan police officer
HJR217 Enrolled
29 arrived, and Lieutenant Hopkins provided cover for the
30 barbershop entrance while the officer relocated the injured
31 man; as they reached cover, several additional Dothan police
32 officers arrived; Lieutenant Hopkins gathered backup, and
33 the group proceeded to clear the barbershop, ensuring the
34 safety of its occupants; and
35 WHEREAS, during the clearance, Lieutenant Hopkins
36 observed a semiautomatic pistol in the bathroom, and one
37 individual was taken into custody and escorted out; after
38 securing the area, law enforcement discovered that the rear
39 emergency exit door was unsecured and stationed officers in
40 that area; upon Lieutenant Hopkins' return to the injured
41 man, Dothan Fire Department responders had arrived, and the
42 original officer was assessing his injuries; Lieutenant
43 Hopkins retrieved his first aid bag and, as additional law
44 enforcement officers secured the mall, he ensured that
45 Dillard's employees were cleared from the bathrooms and that
46 their statements were obtained; and
47 WHEREAS, the actions demonstrated by Lieutenant
48 Hopkins embody the core values of courage, honor, and
49 sacrifice; despite significant personal risk, he acted
50 decisively to protect the lives and safety of others,
51 exemplifying the very highest standards of law enforcement
52 service; and
53 WHEREAS, beyond this heroic act, Lieutenant Hopkins
54 has maintained an outstanding record of service with the
55 Houston County Sheriff's Office, earning the respect of
56 peers, supervisors, and community members alike; now
Page 2

peers, supervisors, and community members alike; now
HJR217 Enrolled
57 therefore,
58 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
59 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That Houston County Sheriff's
60 Lieutenant Robert Hopkins is duly recognized with the
61 Legislative Medal of Honor for Law Enforcement Officers for
62 his integrity, compassion, and commitment to duty, as these
63 attributes reflect credit not only upon him but upon the
64 entire law enforcement profession.
65 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, That this resolution be
66 entered into the official record as a lasting tribute to
67 Lieutenant Robert Hopkins' exemplary leadership and enduring
68 impact on the residents of Houston County.
